g.text: 1. Inverted sew the top line of both tail pieces together.​​2. Leaving a gap, inverted sew the bottom curve of both tail pieces together.​​ Uninvert the tail through either gap so that the outside is out.​​3. Inverted sew the top and bottom edges of the left wing together.​​ Uninvert the wing.​​4. Inverted sew the top and bottom edges of the right wing together.​​ Uninvert the wing.​​5. Working from the beak towards the body, inverted sew one side of the body to the top of the body.​​ As you approach the main body, sew the top of the body to the top of the wing.​​6. Sew the side of the body to the bottom of the wing, then reconnect to the top of the body.​7. Repeat step 5 for the other side of the body.​8. Repeat step 6 for the other side of the body.​9. Inverted sew the side of the body's bottom half to the bottom of the body.​10. Repeat step 9 for the other side of the body.​11. Keeping the body inverted, attach the tail.​​ Uninvert the body through the unsewn back tip of the body.​​​You're nearly there!
